From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: tim2tox-bootstrap <bootstrap@local>
Date: Wed, 20 May 2026 09:10:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 11/11] _handleGlobalCallback: broaden multi-instance
 binary-listener passthrough

Extension of 0008's `passthroughCallbacks` carve-out to cover four more
callback types that suffer from the same architectural mismatch: the
binary-replacement path's SDK-listener and advanced-msg-listener
channels.

`NativeLibraryManager._handleGlobalCallback` dispatches every callback
with an `instance_id` to `Tim2ToxSdkPlatform.dispatchInstanceGlobalCallback`
and then early-returns for non-zero instances (so the SDK singleton
doesn't double-fire on instance 0). 0008 carved out
`FriendAddRequest` + `GroupTipsEvent` so listeners registered via the
SDK singleton (`TIMFriendshipManager.instance.addFriendListener` /
`TIMGroupManager.instance.addGroupListener`) still fire on non-zero
instances. tim2tox auto_tests and toxee use the singleton pattern for
those listener categories.

The same mismatch affects:

  * `OnUserStatusChanged` — auto_tests register via
    `TIMManager.instance.addSDKListener` which populates the singleton
    `v2TimSDKListenerList`, not the platform's per-instance map.
    Without passthrough, `scenario_user_status_virtual_test` times out.
  * `SelfInfoUpdated` — same singleton path. Without passthrough,
    `scenario_events_virtual_test` times out.
  * `UserInfoChanged` — same singleton path. Added defensively because
    the production usage pattern (SDKListener) is identical to the
    above two. No test currently asserts on it, but the symmetry is
    the right shape.
  * `ReceiveNewMessage` — auto_tests register via
    `TIMMessageManager.instance.addAdvancedMsgListener` which
    populates the singleton `_advancedMessageListener`, not the
    platform's per-instance map. Without passthrough,
    `scenario_avatar_virtual_test` times out (waiting for the avatar-
    update message to land in `onRecvNewMessage`).

Double-dispatch risk in clients that use BOTH paths simultaneously
(toxee — uses platform for history + binary for UIKit listeners):

  * `ReceiveNewMessage`: `BinaryReplacementHistoryHook.saveMessage`
    (dart/lib/utils/binary_replacement_history_hook.dart) already
    dedups via msgID match + content/sender/timestamp fallback within
    a 2-second window. Duplicate dispatches are suppressed before
    they reach persistence. The binary-path listener (UIKit fan-out)
    expects to receive the event on instance 0, which is the only
    instance toxee ever runs at — non-zero instances only exist in
    auto_tests. So in practice, toxee never sees a non-zero instance
    here at all, and the new passthrough has zero effect on toxee.
  * `UserStatusChanged` / `SelfInfoUpdated` / `UserInfoChanged`:
    same observation — toxee runs at instance 0 exclusively. The
    passthrough only changes behavior for the multi-instance test
    runner.

Net result: auto_tests in Phase 6 / Phase 7 / Phase 12 that wait for
these singleton-side callbacks now receive them. toxee is unaffected.
---
 .../bindings/native_library_manager.dart      | 22 ++++++++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 21 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/lib/native_im/bindings/native_library_manager.dart b/lib/native_im/bindings/native_library_manager.dart
--- a/lib/native_im/bindings/native_library_manager.dart
+++ b/lib/native_im/bindings/native_library_manager.dart
@@ -377,11 +377,33 @@
       // Without GroupTipsEvent in this list, the multi-instance test path
       // (Tim2ToxSdkPlatform.dispatchInstanceGlobalCallback) early-returns on
       // `grpList.isEmpty` and the event is lost — tests waiting for
       // onGroupInvited / onMemberInvited / onGroupCreated time out.
+      //
+      // The same architectural mismatch affects SDK-listener / advanced-msg
+      // listener channels. Phase 6/7/12 virtual tests register listeners via
+      // `TIMManager.instance.addSDKListener` (singleton `v2TimSDKListenerList`)
+      // and `TIMMessageManager.instance.addAdvancedMsgListener` (singleton
+      // `_advancedMessageListener`), not via the platform's per-instance
+      // listener maps. Without passthrough the events are dropped and tests
+      // timeout waiting for OnUserStatusChanged / SelfInfoUpdated /
+      // UserInfoChanged / ReceiveNewMessage.
+      //
+      // Double-dispatch risk in clients using BOTH paths (toxee): the
+      // platform-side listeners fire first and the SDK singleton then fires.
+      // For ReceiveNewMessage, `BinaryReplacementHistoryHook` dedups via
+      // msgID + (fromUserId, text, isSelf, timestamp within 2s), so duplicate
+      // saves are suppressed before they touch persistence. For SDK status
+      // events (UserStatusChanged / SelfInfoUpdated / UserInfoChanged) the
+      // singleton listener list is the toxee/UIKit fan-out — running it on a
+      // non-zero instance is the desired behavior, identical to instance 0.
       const passthroughCallbacks = <int>{};
       final shouldPassthrough = callbackType ==
               GlobalCallbackType.FriendAddRequest.value ||
           callbackType == GlobalCallbackType.GroupTipsEvent.value ||
+          callbackType == GlobalCallbackType.UserStatusChanged.value ||
+          callbackType == GlobalCallbackType.SelfInfoUpdated.value ||
+          callbackType == GlobalCallbackType.UserInfoChanged.value ||
+          callbackType == GlobalCallbackType.ReceiveNewMessage.value ||
           passthroughCallbacks.contains(callbackType);
       if (instanceId != 0 && !shouldPassthrough) {
         return;
